    <stitle>HENDRICKSON AIR SUSPENSION WITH TRAILING LEAF SPRINGS - AIR SPRING MOUNTING BRACKET (Figure 12 ) - INSTALL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Grease the bore of the air spring mounting bracket with chassis grease and insert cross
                tube.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lower both air spring mounting brackets and guide bolts of air spring mounting brackets into
                main support members.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install washers and locknuts which connect the air spring mounting brackets to the main
                support members. Tighten the locknuts to 220-300 ft-lbs. (298-406 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk document="s03007_10.xml" xrefid="f0300712">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lower vehicle and remove frame stands.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install shock absorber.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Air up system.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check for air leaks.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
